The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, met with the current and past speakers of the state house of assemblies on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) at an event held in Lagos State today, April 13, 2022.


The event, which was hosted by the Speaker of the Lagos House of Assembly, Mudashiru Obasa, was tagged “Retrospecting Democratic Journey In Nigeria.”
The event came a few days after Vice President Yemi Osinbajo declared his intention to run for president of Nigeria in 2023.
Osinbajo’s declaration has generated a lot of reactions on social media as many Tinubu loyalists have tagged him as a betrayal.
The Vice President also met with members of the Nigerian Senate on the platform of the ruling party at the Villa on Tuesday, April 12, 2022. He will also meet with members of the House of Representatives today, Wednesday, April 13, 2022.
